title: Race of Life
subTitle: With predators always looking for a meal, their prey must constantly avoid being eaten. Defensive adaptations add to their chances of survival.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: Attack and escape scenarios involving avian predators and their prey, including horizontal speeding and diving to avoid capture.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: Crocodiles are descended from animals that roamed Earth 250 million years ago, while snakes rely on the sun to control their temperature.

title: Hot Life Africa
subTitle: Being thin, having black patches on light-coloured fur, hyperventilating and licking itself regularly to evaporate saliva are the cheetah's most effective tricks to cope with its scorching environment.

title: Hot Life Africa
subTitle: Many species that live in extreme places slow down their cycles of reproduction and breeding. Wild dogs speed up the process by several weeks to avoid having to expose their pups to the dangers of heat.

title: The Americas
subTitle: The Atlantic Coast, where wild horses battle, bald eagles chase ospreys and sharks protect fish; raccoons navigate city life, black bears search for food in ancient forests and a 130-year-old oak tree prepares for winter's arrival.

title: The Americas
subTitle: Mexico, where deserts meet tropics; see new footage of fledgling pygmy owls, orca hunting, new species in flooded caves and orchid bees filmed in incredible detail -- all revealing the hidden lives of unique wildlife.

title: Parenthood
subTitle: Parenting in the ocean demands dedication and intelligence. From navigating the reef, to teaching young to hunt giants, these parents have remarkable strategies.

title: The Leopardess
subTitle: The Serengeti and its labyrinth of gallery forests are the home of a leopardess. To her family she is both caring provider and fearless defender. For her prey she is sudden death, for her son the only chance to survive in this unforgiving wilderness.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: From insects that look like leaves and snakes that play dead to flying fish and deadly toads, discover the many ways creatures defend themselves against predators.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: From a lionfish's deadly spines to the lightning speed of a barracuda sea creatures have adapted extreme methods and incredible weapons for survival.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: There are many fine examples of evolutionary history in the natural world. Animals adapt through a series of small, random mutations and usually do so in order to compete more effectively for food, water and space. Crocodiles are certainly of an ancient lineage, they are believed to be 200 million years old. Sharks have gone through the process of adaptation and evolutionary experimentation as well.

title: Nature's Survivors
subTitle: Exploring how mountain goats know a volcano is about to erupt, what happens to birds trapped in the eye of a cyclone, and a range of other topics concerning how animals cope with natural disasters.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: A showcase of some of wildlife's most remarkable moments, caught on film by amateurs and professionals. We reveal the full spectrum of animal behaviour: the brutal, the beautiful and the bizarre. Each moment is explained by experts in the field.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: The neotropical forests of South America, extend across territories with an incredible diversity of trees and plants, and are home to jaguars, monkeys and iguanas.

title: River Monsters
subTitle: Jeremy Wade visits Australia's Fitzroy River in search of one of the worlds rarest and least known fish: the Northern River Shark. It's so elusive that only 20 have been caught.

title: Project Tiger
subTitle: The director highlights the incredible comeback of tigers, from a dwindling population due to hunting and poaching to thriving in their wild habitats once more.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: South Africa's Drakensberg is one of the continent's most impressive landscapes. It is home to sharp climatic and ecological gradients as physical conditions change for both land-based creatures and the Raptors that swirl in the skies above.

subTitle: Africa is host to many environments and landscapes; many tribes have refused to abandon their traditional way of life, and animals have been required to change their lives to survive.

subTitle: An exploration of the diversity of Africa's wildlife, highlighting unique aspects.
